{"key":"post-10705050","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10705050</id>\n<content>If you do the initial rinse in HOT tap water, the grains are semi-pasteurized and can't sprout during the soak.&amp;nbsp; 4 to 24 hours is fine, but over 24 and your success rate will drop because too many of the bacterial endospores will germinate and form new endospores by then.&amp;nbsp; If you don't soak long enough, you risk popping the grains during the boil.&amp;nbsp; The key is to soak just long enough so you soften the kernels and get no burst grains when you boil.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10707378</next>\n<prev>10704874</prev>\n<first>10704658</first>\n<last>10714353</last>\n<when>1248044211</when>\n<utime>07/20/09 01:56 AM</utime>\n</post>"}